procedure WFCalculate(inOut Result : tWFNum8) var amount : Num8 var collisionPremium : Num8 var comprehensivePremium : Num8
collisionPremium = self.Vehicle__Price / 98 amount = self.Option__ItemDeductibleValue('Deductible: Collision Coverage') if amount = 250 collisionPremium -= 20 elseif amount = 500 collisionPremium -= 45 elseif amount = 1000 collisionPremium -= 77 endIf ; comprehensivePremium = self.Vehicle__Price / 98 amount = self.Option__ItemDeductibleValue('Deductible: Comprehensive Coverage') if amount = 250 comprehensivePremium -= 20 elseif amount = 500 comprehensivePremium -= 45 elseif amount = 1000 comprehensivePremium -= 77 endIf ; Result = collisionPremium / 2 + comprehensivePremium / 2 endProc

; aWF_RT_Formule (aWPnC_ItemRuleEngine) (Def Version:3) (Implem Version:1)
uses WFTypes, aWFRuleDesc
function RentalReimbursementDaysLimit(Limit : Int4) return tWFNum8 uses aWFStandAloneRule
var tmpRule : aWFRuleDesc
tmpRule = self.GetExactRuleToExecuteFromRankInRuleDesc(0, self.CurrentDate) if tmpRule <> Nil aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).AppendParam(Limit, 0, tmpRule) tmpRule.GetStandAloneResult(_Result, self) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).CleanParamsAfterExecution(tmpRule) else self.AppendComment('No rule version defined at this date') endIf endFunc
function RentalReimbursementLimitPerDay(Limit : Int4) return tWFNum8 uses aWFStandAloneRule
var tmpRule : aWFRuleDesc
tmpRule = self.GetExactRuleToExecuteFromRankInRuleDesc(1, self.CurrentDate) if tmpRule <> Nil aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).AppendParam(Limit, 0, tmpRule) tmpRule.GetStandAloneResult(_Result, self) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).CleanParamsAfterExecution(tmpRule) else self.AppendComment('No rule version defined at this date') endIf endFunc
procedure WFCalculate(inOut Result : tWFNum8) var Memory1 : Num8 var memory2 : Num8 var memory3 : Num8 var NbDaysLimit : Num8 var PerDayLimit : Num8 var LimitGlobal : Num8
Memory1 = 1.32 / 100 LimitGlobal = self.Option__ItemLimitValue('Rental Reimb. Limit Total') self.AppendComment(Concat('Rental Reimbursement: Limit: ', NaS(LimitGlobal))) PerDayLimit = self.Option__ItemLimitValue('Rental Reimb. Limit Per Day') self.AppendComment(Concat('Rental Reimbursement: Limit per Day: ', NaS(PerDayLimit))) NbDaysLimit = LimitGlobal / PerDayLimit memory2 = self.RentalReimbursementDaysLimit(Int4(NbDaysLimit)) memory3 = self.RentalReimbursementLimitPerDay(Int4(PerDayLimit)) Result = Memory1 * memory3 * memory2 Result = self.RoundToNearest(Result, 0.01) endProc

The limit per day is not checked automatically by wynsure. The global limit as a normal limit.
$30 a day limit for a total of $900; for example. So, if you need to rent a car because of an accident, you are maxed out at $900.

procedure WFCalculate(inOut Result : Num8) var LimitPerDay : Num8
